{"serial": "29002", "department_serial": 28, "code": "AS6047", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Observational Astronomy", "ch": "觀測天文學"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chen, Ting-Wan"], "ch": ["陳婷琬"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["5", "6", "7"]}, "loc": {"building": "S4", "room": "914"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "天文研究所碩士班", "en": "MSc in Astronomy"}, "system": {"ch": "碩博同修", "en": "Master/Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 13, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "該課程旨在為碩博士生提供觀測天文學的基礎知識和實踐技能。", "en": "The course aims to provide graduate students with basic knowledge and practical skills in observational astronomy"}, "outline": {"ch": "天文學是一門觀測的科學。本課程預計教授天文觀測的基礎知識，介紹常見的天文觀測儀器，以及常用的觀測技術，會著重在可見光波段。本課程會帶領學生至鹿林天文台實際觀測與操作望遠鏡，引導學生設計和執行天文觀測計畫，並對觀測數據進行處理和分析、包含光度測量等。\n本課程優先開放給天文所碩博生，其他系所學生請優先選修 “PH3045-天文觀測 I”。", "en": "Astronomy is a science of observation. This course aims to provide an overview on the fundamental concepts and techniques in observational astronomy, with a focus on the optical. The course will provide students with hands-on experience in conducting observations and operating telescopes at the Lulin Observatory. Students will be guided in designing and executing astronomical observation projects and will learn data reduction and analysis techniques, including photometry measurements.\nThis course is primarily open to graduate students in the Institute of Astronomy. Students from other departments are encouraged to enroll in “PH3045-Astronomical Observation I“ instead."}, "textbook": {"ch": "Observational Astrophysics, by Lena, Rouan, Lebrun, Mignard ＆ Pelat (translated by Lyle), Springer.  Observational Astronomy: Techniques and Instrumentation, by Sutton, Cambridge.  Handbook of CCD Astronomy, by Howell, Cambridge.", "en": "Observational Astrophys